, from the hard, awesomely dangerous mill work to the dances, picnics, and other recreations that offered welcome diversions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aCity and town lifezTexasxHistory. 0aLumberingzTexasxHistory. 0aSawmillszTexasxHistory. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aConrad, James H., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/77725540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292799882423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292799882/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK